onal stories told by Johnny Neyelle, a Dene Elder from Déline, Northwest Territories. Johnny used storytelling to teach Dene youth and others to understand and celebrate Dene traditions and knowledge. Johnny’s voice makes his stories accessible to readers young and old, and his wisdom reinforces the right way to live: in harmony with people and places. Storytelling forms the core of Dene knowledge-keeping, making this a vital book for Dene people of today and tomorrow, researchers working with Indigenous cultures and oral histories, and all those dedicated to preserving Elders’ stories.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChipewyan IndianszNorthwest TerritoriesvFolklore. 0aChipewyan IndianszNorthwest TerritoriesxHistory. 0aOral traditionzNorthwest Territories. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Indigenous Studies.2bisacsh  aIndigenous Studies / Oral History.1 aFletcher, Alana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNeyelle, Johnny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeyelle, Morris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeyelle, Morris, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212468240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772124682423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772124682/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles